        "(a) &lt; (d) &lt; (c) &lt; (b)",
        "(d) &lt; (a) &lt; (c) &lt; (b)"
      ],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "acid-and-base-strength",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "When stability of nucleophile increases then nucleophilicity decreases.\n<br><br>Stability order :\n<br>H<sub>2</sub>O &gt; CH<sub>3</sub>SO<sub>3</sub><sup>$$-$$</sup> &gt; CH<sub>3</sub>CO<sub>2</sub><sup>$$-$$</sup> &gt; $$\\mathop O\\limits^ -  H$$\n<br><br>So Nucleophilicity order :\n<br>H<sub>2</sub>O &lt; CH<sub>3</sub>SO<sub>3</sub><sup>$$-$$</sup> &lt; CH<sub>3</sub>CO<sub>2</sub><sup>$$-$$</sup> &lt; $$\\mathop O\\limits^ -  H$$",
