      "id": "mnrm67dg",
      "questionNumber": 10,
      "questionText": "<p>In IUPAC nomenclature, the <b>correct</b> order of decreasing priority of functional group is :</p>",
      "options": [
        "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mnrm4psk/d09a6c60-65c3-4546-a444-cc49975c65a9/16d9a540-3426-11f1-8494-df56b9b65369/file-6y3zli1mnrm4psl.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mnrm4psk/d09a6c60-65c3-4546-a444-cc49975c65a9/16d9a540-3426-11f1-8494-df56b9b65369/file-6y3zli1mnrm4psl.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 2nd April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 13 English Option 1\">",
        "$$\n-\\mathrm{CONH}_2,-\\mathrm{COOCH}_3,-\\mathrm{CHO},-\\mathrm{NH}_2,-\\mathrm{OH}\n$$",
        "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mnrm4lhw/3f72327e-7343-45ad-83c4-b9bcf19d57f7/13880940-3426-11f1-8494-df56b9b65369/file-6y3zli1mnrm4lhx.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mnrm4lhw/3f72327e-7343-45ad-83c4-b9bcf19d57f7/13880940-3426-11f1-8494-df56b9b65369/file-6y3zli1mnrm4lhx.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 2nd April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 13 English Option 3\">",
        "$$\n-\\mathrm{CONH}_2,-\\mathrm{CHO},-\\mathrm{CN},-\\mathrm{NH}_2,-\\mathrm{C} \\equiv \\mathrm{C}-\n$$"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "iupac-nomenclature",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<table class=\"tg\" style=\"undefined;table-layout: fixed; width: 711px\">\n<colgroup>\n<col style=\"width: 59px\">\n<col style=\"width: 199px\">\n<col style=\"width: 278px\">\n<col style=\"width: 175px\">\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-7btt\"></th>\n    <th class=\"tg-7btt\">Functional group (priority order)</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-7btt\">suffix(s)</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-7btt\">prefix</th>\n  </tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(1)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 2nd April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 13 English Explanation 1\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpnphcp/3a244065-8715-4bb9-8b04-0419903a872e/b56b0090-8f35-11ec-a918-532e52a0063e/file-1kzpnphcq.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpnphcp/3a244065-8715-4bb9-8b04-0419903a872e/b56b0090-8f35-11ec-a918-532e52a0063e/file-1kzpnphcq.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh\"> </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>Oic acid</b>(when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain)<br>or<br><b>Carboxylic acid</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">Carboxy</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(2)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 2nd April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 13 English Explanation 2\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpnzht2/441ed497-3450-4ea2-9a04-0c56068636cd/cbdc6f70-8f36-11ec-a918-532e52a0063e/file-1kzpnzht3.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpnzht2/441ed497-3450-4ea2-9a04-0c56068636cd/cbdc6f70-8f36-11ec-a918-532e52a0063e/file-1kzpnzht3.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh\"> </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">sulphonic acid</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">sulpho</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(3)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 2nd April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 13 English Explanation 3\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpo1x19/95ae67d6-ffec-4705-9a44-f999c83fb334/0f3de2d0-8f37-11ec-a918-532e52a0063e/file-1kzpo1x1a.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpo1x19/95ae67d6-ffec-4705-9a44-f999c83fb334/0f3de2d0-8f37-11ec-a918-532e52a0063e/file-1kzpo1x1a.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh\"> </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>Oic anhydrid</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain) <br>or<br><b>Carboxylic anhydride</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">$$ - $$</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(4)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 2nd April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 13 English Explanation 4\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpvjtwd/7f6f089d-c6fe-48b9-a1c4-595a3e306171/6149bcd0-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvjtwe.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpvjtwd/7f6f089d-c6fe-48b9-a1c4-595a3e306171/6149bcd0-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvjtwe.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh\"></td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>Oate</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain) <br>or<br><b>Carboxylate</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">$$ - $$</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(5)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 2nd April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 13 English Explanation 5\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpvhyj3/f2fd0132-de26-476f-a616-bb759c9e8742/2d3f49f0-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvhyj4.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpvhyj3/f2fd0132-de26-476f-a616-bb759c9e8742/2d3f49f0-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvhyj4.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh\"> </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>Oyl halide</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain) <br>or<br><b>Carboxyl halide</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">haloflormyl</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(6)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 2nd April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 13 English Explanation 6\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpvmmrd/c937a359-3ffe-4683-9bd3-3074eee29a56/af336a90-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvmmre.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpvmmrd/c937a359-3ffe-4683-9bd3-3074eee29a56/af336a90-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvmmre.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh\"></td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>amide</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain) <br>or<br><b>carbamide</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">carbamoyl</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(7)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">cynide ($$ - $$ C $$ \\equiv $$ N)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>nitrile</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain) <br>or<br><b>carbonitrile</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">cyano</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(8)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 2nd April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 13 English Explanation 7\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpvotae/df9c34e4-532f-4453-a80e-a39f58a78c6f/ebdcbe60-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvotaf.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpvotae/df9c34e4-532f-4453-a80e-a39f58a78c6f/ebdcbe60-8f54-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvotaf.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh\"></td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">Carbylamine</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">isocyano</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(9)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 2nd April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 13 English Explanation 8\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpvr75i/aa709c39-b3cb-474c-a088-787493f284bd/2e30b960-8f55-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvr75j.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpvr75i/aa709c39-b3cb-474c-a088-787493f284bd/2e30b960-8f55-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvr75j.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh\"></td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"><b>al</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group present in the main chain) <br>or<br><b>Carbaldehyde</b> (when carbon(C) of this functional group is not present in the main chain) </td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">formyl (oxo)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(10)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\"> <img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 2nd April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 13 English Explanation 9\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1kzpvsokz/b5b4a5c1-59e5-4cd2-8160-01d5ef423466/5776ac30-8f55-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvsol0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1kzpvsokz/b5b4a5c1-59e5-4cd2-8160-01d5ef423466/5776ac30-8f55-11ec-9257-c58bf97b0f56/file-1kzpvsol0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh\"></td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">one</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">oxo</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(11)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">$$ - $$ OH</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">ol</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">hydroxy</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(12)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">$$ - $$ SH</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">thiol</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">mercapto</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">(13)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">$$ - $$ NH$$_2$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">amine</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-0pky\">amino</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>From this table you can see -COOH has highest priority and -NH<sub>2</sub> has lowest priority among all functional groups.</p>",
